Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Brother 'Ali Salim al-Bid, vice chairman of the 
Presidential Council, received in Aden at noon today brother Dr. 
Fayiz al-Rabi', the Jordanian ambassador to our country, to make 
his acquaintance. During the meeting, they reviewed the 
brotherly relations between our country and Jordan. They also 
exchanged views on the current situation and developments. 
  Brother 'Ali Salim al-Bid appreciated the efforts that His 
Majesty King Husayn Bin-Talal of the Hashemite Kingdom of Jordan 
and other brothers in Jordan have exerted to help our country 
overcome the difficulties and obstacles that are facing the 
march of unity and democracy. He also appreciated their 
eagerness to bolster stability in our country. He stressed the 
importance of bolstering the brotherly bilateral relations and 
expanding the scope of cooperation in the service of the common 
interests of the brotherly Yemeni and Jordanian peoples. 
  At the end of the meeting, the brother vice chairman asked 
the Jordanian ambassador to convey his greetings to his Majesty 
King Husayn and his wishes for his majesty's continued health 
and happiness and for Jordanian people continued progress. 

